# Core Standards

- Minimize scope — small, focused diffs over broad refactors
- Match existing naming, types, and folder conventions before introducing new patterns
- Reuse and extend existing code; do not duplicate logic
- Business logic belongs in `service.ts`, never in UI components
- Comments only for non-obvious business logic or security constraints
- Never commit secrets (`.env`, credentials, API keys)
- Only create git commits when explicitly requested
